2Famp_articleshow%2F108666640.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Political%20Earthquake%E2%80%99%20shakes%20up%20succession%20fight%20in%20Vietnam%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710997774000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108666594%2Cimgsize-28640.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fpolitical-earthquake-shakes-up-succession-fight-in-vietnam%2Farticleshow%2F108666414.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F108666414.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EVietnam%20grapples%20with%20President%20Vo%20Van%20Thuong's%20resignation%20amid%20Communist%20Party%20power%20struggles%2C%20affecting%20the%20growing%20economy.%20Stability%20in%20Vietnamese%20stocks%20and%20currency%20prevails%20amidst%20ongoing%20anti-corruption%20probes%20and%20controversies%20surrounding%20Minister%20of%20Public%20Security%20To%20Lam.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fpolitical-earthquake-shakes-up-succession-fight-in-vietnam%2Farticleshow%2F108666414.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fpolitical-earthquake-shakes-up-succession-fight-in-vietnam%2Famp_articleshow%2F108666414.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fpolitical-earthquake-shakes-up-succession-fight-in-vietnam%2Famp_articleshow%2F108666414.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Developing%20Country%2C%20Security%20Fears%3A%20Centre%20Rejects%20Rohingya%20Right%20To%20Stay%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20developing%20country%20that%20is%20also%20the%20world's%20most%20populated%2C%20India%20needs%20to%20prioritise%20its%20own%20citizens%2C%20the%20Centre%20has%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20asserting%20that%20the%20illegal%20migration%20of%20and%20stay%20and%20Rohingya%20refugees%20have%20serious%20ramifications%20for%20national%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20affidavit%20filed%20yesterday%20was%20in%20response%20to%20a%20petition%20seeking%20a%20direction%20to%20the%20Centre%20to%20release%20Rohingya%20refugees%20put%20in%20detention%20for%20alleged%20violation%20of%20the%20Foreigners%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Rohingya%20refugees%2C%20most%20of%20them%20Muslims%2C%20have%20fled%20ethnic%20violence%20in%20Buddhist-majority%20Myanmar%20and%20entered%20India%2C%20Bangladesh%20and%20other%20countries%20illegally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Rohingya%20refugees%20are%20now%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20a%20fresh%20political%20row%20over%20the%20Centre's%20implementation%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20(CAA)%20to%20offer%20citizenship%20to%20non-Muslim%20migrants%20from%20Bangladesh%2C%20Pakistan%20and%20Afghanistan%2C%20who%20fled%20religious%20persecution%20in%20these%20countries%20and%20entered%20India%20before%202015.%20Hitting%20back%20at%20the%20Opposition%20for%20raising%20the%20question%20of%20national%20security%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20implementation%20of%20CAA%2C%20Union%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20has%20questioned%20why%20Opposition%20leaders%20are%20not%20opposing%20Rohingya's%20entry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20affidavit%2C%20the%20Centre%20has%20said%20India%20is%20not%20a%20signatory%20to%20the%201951%20Refugee%20Convention%20and%20to%20the%20protocol%20relating%20to%20the%20Status%20of%20Refugees%2C%201967.%20Therefore%2C%20whether%20or%20not%20any%20class%20of%20persons%20are%20to%20be%20recognised%20as%20refugees%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bpure%20policy%20decision%26quot%3B%2C%20it%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEffectively%2C%20the%20prayers%20therein%20are%20seeking%20to%20provide%20illegal%20Rohingya%20migrants%20with%20the%20right%20to%20reside%20within%20the%20territory%20of%20India%2C%20which%20is%20expressly%20against%20Article%2019%20(freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20expression).%20It%20is%20submitted%20that%20Article%2019%20is%20limited%20in%20its%20application%20only%20to%20citizens%20and%20cannot%20be%20extended%20to%20apply%20to%20foreigners%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre%20has%20also%20said%20no%20community%20can%20be%20granted%20refugee%20status%20outside%20the%20legislative%20framework%20and%20such%20a%20declaration%20cannot%20be%20made%20by%20a%20judicial%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20developing%20country%20with%20the%20largest%20population%20in%20the%20world%20and%20with%20limited%20resources%2C%20priority%20is%20required%20to%20be%20given%20to%20the%20country's%20own%20citizens.%20Therefore%2C%20there%20cannot%20be%20any%20blanket%20acceptance%20of%20foreigners%20as%20refugees%20especially%20where%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20such%20foreigners%20have%20entered%20the%20country%20illegally%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre%20has%20cited%20a%202005%20verdict%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20stress%20the%20dangers%20of%20unchecked%20immigration.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20submitted%20that%20continuance%20of%20Rohingyas'%20illegal%20migration%20into%20India%20and%20their%20continued%20stay%20in%20India%2C%20apart%20from%20being%20absolutely%20illegal%2C%20is%20found%20to%20be%20having%20serious%20national%20security%20ramifications%20and%20has%20serious%20security%20threats%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre's%20affidavit%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20India%20has%20unfenced%20borders%20with%20Nepal%2C%20Bhutan%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20Myanmar%20etc.%20and%20an%20easily%20navigable%20sea%20route%20with%20Pakistan%20as%20well%20as%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20making%20it%20vulnerable%20to%20a%20continuous%20threat%20of%20an%20influx%20of%20illegal%20migration%20and%20resultant%20problems%20arising%20therefrom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20grant%20of%20any%20status%20qua%20immigration%20to%20persons%20or%20a%20class%20of%20persons%20coming%20from%20a%20particular%20country%20is%20not%20just%20a%20national%20issue%20but%20essentially%20an%20outcome%20of%20political%20decisions%20of%20the%20State%20in%20respect%20of%20maintaining%20its%20foreign%20relations%20with%20the%20State%20in%20question%20or%20with%20any%20other%20foreign%20nations.%20Such%20a%20decision%20is%20often%20a%20product%20of%20complex%20interplay%20of%20diverse%20factors%20such%20as%20social%2C%20economic%2C%20cultural%20and%20often%20extra-legal%20or%20extra%20judicial%20considerations.%20In%20light%20of%20the%20above%2C%20prayers%20in%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20present%20which%20seek%20to%20alter%20the%20existing%20regime%20are%20not%20maintainable%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20it%20is%20accepted%20that%20Rohingyas%20are%20illegal%20migrants%2C%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Foreigners%20Act%2C%201946%20would%20apply%20to%20them%20in%20full%20force%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20prayer%20in%20the%20petition%20would%20essentially%20amount%20to%20putting%20the%20Foreigners%20Act%20itself%20in%20abeyance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20prayer%20of%20the%20petitioner%20amounts%20to%20re-writing%20of%20the%20statute%20or%20directing%20the%20Parliament%20to%20frame%20a%20law%20in%20a%20particular%20manner%20which%20is%20wholly%20beyond%20the%20powers%20of%20judicial%20review.%20It%20is%20trite%20law%20that%20the%20courts%20cannot%20direct%20Parliament%20to%20make%20a%20law%20or%20to%20legislate%20in%20a%20particular%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20affidavit%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710997620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fcq5c2cmg_supreme-court-reuters_625x300_06_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frohingya-refugees-supreme-court-developi