20%E2%80%98skilled%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20true%20sense.%20This%20calls%20for%20scrutiny%20of%20performance%20of%20few%20flagship%20schemes%20of%20government%20under%20skill%20development%20(SD)%20initiatives%20in%20India%20and%20underlines%20why%20reforms%20like%20RA%20are%20a%20step%20in%20the%20right%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuantitative%20evidence%20related%20to%20Skill%20India%20Mission%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVocational%20education%20and%20training%20(VET)%20has%20historically%20been%20neglected%20in%20India%20for%20over%20half%20a%20century%20until%20the%202000s%20(just%20as%20school%20education%20had%20remained%20neglected%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20planning%20strategy)%20%E2%80%93%20the%20costs%20of%20which%20we%20continue%20to%20pay%20today.%20In%201991%2C%20during%20the%20liberalisation%20of%20the%20economy%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.pib.gov.in%2Farchive%2Freleases98%2Flyr2003%2Frsep2003%2F06092003%2Fr060920031.html%5C%22%3E52%25%20or%20half%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20population%20was%20illiterate%20and%20mostly%20concentrated%20on%20agriculture%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20school%20education%20received%20a%20newfound%20emphasis%20in%20public%20spending%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20VET%20still%20continued%20to%20be%20neglected%20(although%20that%20was%20not%20the%20case%20for%20technical%20higher%20education).%20The%2011th%20Five%20Year%20Plan%20(2007-12)%20was%20the%20first%20plan%20that%20had%20a%20chapter%20on%20skill%20development.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20this%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20manufacturing%20and%20services%20workforce%20still%20have%20individuals%20with%20very%20low%20levels%20of%20education.%20Worse%2C%20hardly%20any%20worker%20has%20received%20formal%20VET.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20National%20Sample%20Survey%20Organisation%20Employment-Unemployment%20Survey%20(NSSO%20EUS)%202011-12%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmospi.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fpublication_reports%2Fnss_rep_563_13mar15.pdf%5C%22%3Eonly%202.2%25%20of%20the%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20India%20had%20received%20formal%20VET.%20As%20per%20the%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey%20(PLFS)%20data%2C%20the%20percentage%20of%20formally%20vocationally%20trained%20individuals%20decreased%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmospi.gov.in%2Fpublication%2Fannual-report-plfs-2017-18%5C%22%3E2.2%25%20(10.43%20million)%20in%202011-12%20to%202%25%20(9.14%20million)%20in%202017-18%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20rose%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mospi.gov.in%2Fpublication%2Fannual-report-periodic-labour-force-survey-plfs-july-2022-june-2023%5C%22%3E3.7%25%20(21.05%20million)%20in%202022-23%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Additionally%2C%20as%20per%20the%20National%20Scholarship%20Portal%20(NSP)%202015%2C%20only%202.7%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20workforce%20has%20received%20formal%20skill%20training%2C%20compared%20to%2052%25%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%2080%25%20in%20Japan%2C%20and%2096%25%20in%20South%20Korea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202024%20budget%20speech%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20claimed%20that%2014%20million%20individuals%20were%20trained%20under%20the%20Skill%20India%20Mission%2C%20which%20included%20upskilling%20and%20reskilling%205.4%20million.%20But%20in%20reality%2C%20there%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20disconnect%20between%20the%20claims%20of%20the%20government%20and%20the%20ground%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20a%20stark%20disparity%20between%20these%20numbers%20and%20targets%20set%20in%20the%20National%20Policy%20on%20Skill%20Development%20and%20Entrepreneurship%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmsde.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2019-09%2FNational%2520Policy%2520on%2520Skill%2520Development%2520and%2520Entreprenurship%2520Final.pdf%5C%22%3E%C2%A02015%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20aimed%20to%20skill%20400%20million%20workers%20by%202022%C2%A0%20and%20remains%20a%20distant%20dream.%20Importantly%2C%20300%20million%20of%20these%20workers%20were%20to%20be%20given%20Recognition%20of%20Prior%20Learning%20(RPL)%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20required%20since%20over%2095%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20non-farm%20workers%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ilo.org%2Fwcmsp5%2Fgroups%2Fpublic%2F---ed_emp%2F---ifp_skills%2Fdocuments%2Fpublication%2Fwcms_734503.pdf%5C%22%3E%20acquire%20their%20skills%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20unorganised%20sector%20in%20informal%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20these%20skills%20are%20not%20certified%2C%20hence%2C%20not%20recognised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInformal%20learning%20deserves%20recognition%20and%20certification%20so%20that%20such%20workers%20can%20acquire%20some%20dignity%20in%20the%20labour%20market%20and%20certificates%20could%20possibly%20help%20them%20make%20a%20claim%20for%20higher%20wages.%20Hence%2C%20the%20National%20Skill%20Development%20Mission%20(SDM)%20and%20National%20Policy%20on%20Skill%20Development%20and%20Entrepreneurship%20were%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20response%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.msde.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2019-09%2FNational%2520Skill%2520Development%2520Mission.pdf%5C%22%3Eto%20the%20very%20low%20level%20of%20formal%20vocational%20training%20among%20the%20Indian%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E.%20SDM%20was%20implemented%20through%20schemes%20such%20as%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Kaushal%20Vikas%20Yojana%20(PMKVY)%2C%20Deen%20Dayal%20Upadhyaya%20Grameen%20Kaushalya%20Yojana%20(DDUGKY)%20and%20the%20National%20Apprenticeship%20Promotion%20Scheme%20(NAPS)%2C%20to%20address%20employability%20gaps.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fjute-mills-bengal-labour-india-out-of-work%5C%22%3EBengal%E2%80%99s%20Jute%20Mills%20Run%20on%20the%20Labour%20of%20%E2%80%98Zero%20Number%E2%80%99%20Worke%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3Ers%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnit%20level%20analysis%20of%202017-18%20PLFS%20data%20stated%20that%2022%25%20of%20the%20total%20vocationally%20trained%20individuals%20undertook%20less%20than%20six-month%20courses%2C%20and%20that%20share%20has%20now%20risen%20to%2037%25.%20More%20worrying%20is%20that%20in%202017%2C%2029%25%20individuals%20used%20to%20take%20two-year%20or%20longer%20courses%2C%20which%20is%20now%20reduced%20to%2014.29%25.%20There%20is%20a%20rapid%20decrease%20in%20the%20duration%20of%20SD%20courses.%20So%2C%20overall%20more%20people%20are%20getting%20degrees%2Fcertificates%20or%20formal%20education%20but%20the%20duration%20of%20these%20courses%20is%20very%20short%20%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20some%20cases%20only%2010%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EProliferation%20of%20short-term%20training%20to%20project%20large%20increases%20in%20trained%20workers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20the%20logic%20behind%20this%20rise%20in%20short%20term%20training%20(STT)%20in%20formal%20vocational%20education%20%C2%A0when%2C%20according%20to%202017-18%20PLFS%20data%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2FIbid%5C%22%3E96.4%25%20of%20individuals%20in%20India%20spend%20less%20than%2015%20years%20in%20formal%20education%2C%20and%20that%20number%20has%20now%20decreased%20to%2095.8%25.%3C%2Fa%3E%20This%20anomaly%20requires%20a%20theoretical%20deep%20dive%20into%20the%20skilling%20strategy%20adopted%20by%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20flagship%20PMKVY%2C%20the%20official%20website%20data%20claims%20that%2054%25%20of%20the%20trainees%20are%20placed%20through%20this%20scheme.%20Actual%20data%20analysis%20shows%20that%20of%20the%20total%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pmkvyofficial.org%2Fpmkvy2%2FDashboard.php%5C%22%3E12%2C454%2C858%20candidates%20assessed%2C%2011%2C041%2C125%20candidates%20were%20certified%2C%20and%20only%202%2C451%2C517%20candidates%20were%20placed%2C%20i.e.%20only%2022.2%25%20were%20placed%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20PMKVY%20has%20been%20Skill%20India%20Mission%E2%80%99s%20flagship%20programme%20and%20yet%2C%20not%20only%20is%20the%20training%20all%20short%20term%2C%20the%20placement%20rate%20shows%20no%20improvement%20over%20time%3A%20placement%20rate%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pmkvyofficial.org%2Fpmkvy2%2FDashboard.php%5C%22%3EPMKVY%201.0%20(which%20started%20in%202015)%20is%2018.4%25%2C%20PMKVY%202.0%20is%2023.4%25%2C%20and%20PMKVY%203.0%20is%2010.1%25.%3C%2Fa%3E%20However%2C%20the%20programme%20is%20still%20being%20funded%20%E2%80%94%20PMKVY%204%20is%20starting%20this%20year%20with%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiabudget.gov.in%2Fdoc%2Feb%2Fsbe92.pdf%5C%22%3Ebudget%20outlay%20of%20Rs%201%2C200%20crore%20approximately%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sector-wise%20placement%20rate%20showed%20only%2054%25%20for%20electronics%20and%20hardware%20and%2020%25%20for%20apparel%2C%20while%20the%20placement%20rate%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20eight%20sectors%2C%20namely%20construction%2C%20BFSI%2C%20beauty%20and%20wellness%2C%20etc.%2C%20was%20lower%20than%2010%25.%20So%2C%20how%20these%20numbers%20add%20up%20to%2054%25%20is%20anybody%E2%80%99s%20guess.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERemarkably%2C%20ahead%20of%20the%20run%20up%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20the%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA)%20government%20has%20shut%20down%20its%20dashboards%20and%20data%20sources%20in%20the%20last%20month%20%E2%80%93%20why%2C%20we%20are%20left%20to%20guess.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rise%20of%20these%20short-term%20skilling%20courses%20only%20increases%20the%20number%20of%20individuals%20who%20may%20possess%20a%20certificate%20of%20being%20skilled%2C%20but%20in%20reality%2C%20they%20may%20lack%20the%20skills%20to%20carry%20out%20a%20particular%20task%20efficiently%20due%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20proper%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20this%2C%20there%20is%20a%20desperate%20need%20for%20quality%20checks%20of%20these%20short-term%20courses.%20These%20courses%20produce%20half-trained%20workers%2C%20and%20the%20degrees%2Fcertificates%20of%20these%20individuals%20don%E2%80%99t%20carry%20much%20value%20in%20the%20labour%20market%20as%20workers%20essentially%20don%E2%80%99t%20learn%20required%20skills%20through%20these%20courses.%20Thereby%2C%20they%20are%20not%20able%20to%20secure%20a%20job%20after%20completion%20of%20these%20training%20programmes.%20This%20skilling%20system%20produces%20half-educated%20and%20quarter-trained%20personnel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERecognition%20of%20prior%20learning%20in%20National%20Skills%20Policy%20%E2%80%93%20serious%20issues%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20not%20been%20a%20single%20government%20report%20published%20analysing%20the%20efficiency%20and%20quality%20of%20STT%20and%20RPL%20courses%20under%20PMKVY.%20For%20these%20courses%2C%20the%20total%20duration%20can%20be%20as%20short%20as%2024%20hours%20or%203%20days%20of%20training.%20On%20an%20average%2C%20an%20RPL%20course%20is%20for%2015-day%20duration%20(usually%20offered%20by%20the%20NSDC%20funded%20private%20vocational%20training%20providers)%20where%20the%20quality%20of%20these%20courses%20%E2%80%94%20credentials%20of%20the%20training%20providers%2C%20assessment%20agencies%E2%80%99%20diligence%2C%20and%20assessment%20by%20certification%20authority%20%E2%80%94%20is%20highly%20questionable%20along%20with%20numerous%20cases%20of%20forgery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EApprenticeship%20programmes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%201961%2C%20India%20has%20had%20an%20Apprenticeship%20Act%2C%20which%20requires%20all%20registered%20firms%20to%20accept%20apprentices%20for%20at%20least%20one%20year%20or%20more.%20About%20ten%20years%20ago%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FIndias-Skills-Challenge-Vocational-Demographic%2Fdp%2F0199452776%5C%22%3E2%2C50%2C000%20apprentices%20existed%20in%20registered%20non-farm%20enterprises.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2019%2C%202016%2C%20the%20government%20of%20India%20launched%20the%20National%20Apprenticeship%20Promotion%20Scheme%20(NAPS)%2C%20which%20had%20a%20budget%20of%20Rs%2010%2C000%20crore.%20The%20main%20objective%20of%20the%20scheme%20was%20to%20promote%20apprenticeship%20training.%20Though%20the%20target%20was%20to%20train%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressNoteDetails.aspx%3FNoteId%3D149802%5C%22%3E50%20lakh%20apprentices%20by%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdashboard.apprenticeshipindia.org%2F%5C%22%3Eonly%2020%20lakh%20apprentices%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20be%20trained%20by%202022.%20Out%20of%20the%20envisioned%20Rs%2010%2C000%20crore%2C%20only%20around%20Rs%20650%20crore%20were%20disbursed%20to%20the%20states%20between%20the%20period%20of%202017%20to%202022.%20NAPS%202%20was%20launched%20in%202023%2C%20and%20no%20figures%20for%20the%20same%20are%20currently%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20ILO%20study%20in%202022%20concluded%20that%20the%20amendments%20in%20the%201961%20Act%20have%20contributed%20to%20some%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20apprentices%20in%20India.%20Out%20of%20a%20workforce%20of%20570%20million%20in%202022-23%20(as%20per%20PLFS)%2C%20the%20apprentices%20were%20just%20over%20a%20half%20million%2C%20a%20rise%20from%202.5%20lakh%20ten%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClearly%2C%20the%20amendments%20have%20not%20worked%20the%20magic.%20This%20is%20not%20surprising%2C%20given%20practically%20the%20entire%20private%20corporate%20sector%20has%20largely%20ignored%20the%20apprenticeship%20schemes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20the%20central%20and%20state%20public%20enterprises%20have%20tended%20to%20fulfil%20their%20obligations.%20MSMEs%20still%20continue%20to%20ignore%20the%20scheme.%20The%20result%3A%20Germany%2C%20with%20a%2046%20million%20workforce%20has%20at%20least%206%20million%20apprentices%3B%20India%20has%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20half%20a%20million.%20The%20difference%20arises%20from%20the%20industry%2Femployer%20involvement%20in%20pre-employment%20training%20%E2%80%93%20which%20makes%20India%E2%80%99s%20approach%20supply-driven%2C%20but%20successful%20VET%20programmes%20around%20the%20globe%20have%20been%20demand-driven.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20India%E2%80%99s%20youth%20need%20urgently%2C%20as%206%20million%20or%20more%20join%20the%20labour%20force%20each%20year%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20and%20over%20a%20100%20million%20wait%20in%20the%20wings%20as%20Not%20in%20Education%2C%20Employment%20or%20Training%20(NEETs)%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20is%20a%20pathway%20for%20education%20of%20a%20general%20academic%20nature%20or%20vocational%20or%20technical%20manner.%20That%20requires%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20think%20seriously%20and%20urgently%20about%20employers%2Findustry%20in%20the%20skilling%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Futtar-pradesh-exams-cancellations-protests%5C%22%3EMore%20Cancellations%2C%20Over%2050%20Lakhs%20Affected%2C%20Cloud%20Over%20Boards%20Too%3A%20The%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Exam%20Story%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiaeducationforum.org%2Fpdf%2FISR-2021.pdf%5C%22%3EIndia%20Skills%20Report%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%20argues%20that%20nearly%20half%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20graduates%20are%20unemployable.%20Open%20unemployment%20was%20barely%202.1%25%20in%202012%20and%20had%20already%20nearly%20tripled%20to%206.1%25%20in%202018%2C%20the%20highest%20rate%20in%2045%20years%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20labour%20force%20surveys.%C2%A0The%20total%20number%20of%20unemployed%20was%20one%20crore%20in%202012%20before%20the%20BJP%20came%20to%20power%20%E2%80%93%20but%20it%20had%20tripled%20by%202018%20to%20three%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhat-we-know-about-indias-post-covid-economy-recovery-and-rising-inequality%5C%22%3Eyouth%20unemployment%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20went%20through%20the%20roof%20for%20those%3A%20with%20middle%20school%20(class%208)%20education%2C%20rising%20from%204.5%25%20to%2013.7%25%3B%20with%20secondary%20education%20(class%2010)%20from%205.9%25%20to%2014.4%25%3B%20and%20with%20higher%20secondary%20(class%2012)%20education%20from%2010.8%25%20to%2023.8%25.%20Educated%20unemployment%20worsened%20sharply.%20For%20graduates%2C%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20rose%20from%2019.2%25%20to%2035.8%25%3B%20and%20for%20postgraduates%20from%2021.3%25%20to%2036.2%25%20(2022-23).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20light%20of%20educated%20unemployment%2C%20lack%20of%20takers%20of%20skill%20programmes%2C%20low-quality%20training%20and%20abysmal%20placement%20rate%2C%20there%20is%20an%20urgent%20need%20for%20a%20comprehensive%20overhaul%20of%20the%20skill%20development%20landscape.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20which%20is%20already%20suffering%20from%20high%20educated%20unemployment%2C%20in%20the%20future%20is%20moving%20towards%20the%20problem%20of%20skill%20underutilisation%20and%20over-education%20(or%20%E2%80%98degree%20mania%E2%80%99).%20Mere%20rhetoric%20and%20inflated%20statistics%20will%20no%20longer%20suffice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20imperative%20that%20the%20government%20prioritises%20quality%20over%20quantity%2C%20ensuring%20that%20every%20individual%20emerges%20from%20these%20programmes%20truly%20equipped%20to%20contribute%20meaningfully%20to%20the%20workforce.%20Anything%20less%20would%20be%20a%20disservice%20to%20the%20aspirations%20of%20millions%20seeking%20a%20better%20future%20through%20skill%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESkill%20policies%20and%20schemes%20have%20completely%20failed%20and%20need%20a%20big%20overhaul%20on%20the%20lines%20of%20successful%20skill%20formation%20models%20like%20Swiss%20and%20Germanic%20skill%20models%20which%20are%20based%20on%20duality%20principles%20with%20youth%20and%20industry%20at%20centre%20stage.%20A%20Right%20to%20Apprenticeship%20to%20every%20youth%20should%20be%20an%20urgent%20priority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20name%3D%5C%22_ftn1%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fthe-reality-of-skill-india-mission-short-courses-no-employable-skills-and-rise-in-unemploy-ment%23_ftnref1%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESantosh%20Mehrotra%20is%20a%20Research%20Fellow%20in%20IZA%20Institute%20of%20Labour%20Economics%2C%20Bonn%2C%20Germany%20and%20Dr.%20Harshil%20Sharma%20is%20Programme%20Associate%20at%20iForest.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710990012000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F21083408%2FScreenshot-2024-03-21-at-8.30.15.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fthe-reality-of-skill-india-mission-short-courses-no-employable-skills-and-rise-in-unemploy-ment%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20India%20Skills%20Report%202021%20argues%20that%20nearly%20half%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20graduates%20are%20unemployable.%20Open%20unemployment%20was%20barely%202.1%25%20in%202012%20and%20had%20already%20nearly%20tripled%20to%206.1%25%20in%202018%2C%20the%20highest%20rate%20in%2045%20years%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20labour%20force%20surveys.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fthe-reality-of-skill-india-mission-short-courses-no-employable-skills-and-rise-in-unemploy-ment%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Apple%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20access%20manuals%2C%20guides%20for%20iPhone%2C%20Mac%2C%20more%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710989631000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108662757%2Cimgsize-646270.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Fapple-makes-it-easier-to-download-manuals-and-guides-for-iphone-mac-and-more%2Farticleshow%2F108662757.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Apple's%20new%20'Documentation'%20webpage%20centralizes%20access%20to%20user%20guides%2C%20tech%20specs%2C%20and%20software%20downloads%20for%20all%20products%2C%20providi